# Events checks

* Go to the login page
* I log in as "admin" with "opencast"
* I am logged in as "Opencast Project Administrator"
* I select the admin language dropdown
* I set the current translation to "English"
* I open the hamburger
* I click the "Recordings" section
* I open the "Events" pane

## Minimum viable event

* I record the number of results
* I open the new event modal
* I set the title to "Test title" in the event modal
* the Next button is enabled in the "event" modal
* I click Next in the "event" modal
* I upload "/home/greg/opencast/mediapackages/mh_demo/nonsegment-audio.mpg" as presenter video
* the Next button is enabled in the "event" modal
* I upload "/home/greg/opencast/mediapackages/mh_demo/segment.mpg" as slide video
* I click Next in the "event" modal
* I select "Process upon upload and schedule" in the new event workflow dropdown
* I set the "flagQuality360p" workflow flag to "true"
* I set the "flagQuality720p" workflow flag to "false"
* I click Next in the "event" modal
* I select "public" in the new event acl dropdown
* I click Next in the "event" modal
* I verify my selections on the event confirmation modal
* I click Create in the "event" modal
* I check that the number of results has increased by 1
* I wait until the event has uploaded

